<topic id='element_organisation_code__code_of_provider_.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Element: ORGANISATION CODE (CODE OF PROVIDER) - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
    <dl>
      <dlentry>
        <dt>Format / Length</dt>
        <dd>an3, an5 or an6</dd>
      </dlentry>
    </dl>

  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_organisation_code__code_of_provider_">ORGANISATION CODE (CODE OF PROVIDER)</xref>
 is the same as the attribute 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_code">ORGANISATION CODE</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_organisation_code__code_of_provider_">ORGANISATION CODE (CODE OF PROVIDER)</xref>
 is the 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_code">ORGANISATION CODE</xref>
 of the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
 acting as a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Provider</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
For 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/navigation/commissioning_data_sets_menu.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Commissioning Data Sets</xref>
, the 
    <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_organisation_code__code_of_provider_">ORGANISATION CODE (CODE OF PROVIDER)</xref>
 should always be the 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_code">ORGANISATION CODE</xref>
 of the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Provider</xref>
 receiving the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/national_tariff_payment_system.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">National_Tariff_Payment_System</xref>
 income.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_organisation_code__code_of_provider_">ORGANISATION CODE (CODE OF PROVIDER)</xref>
 is used by the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/secondary_uses_service.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Secondary_Uses_Service</xref>
 to derive the 
    <b>
         <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/healthcare_resource_group.asp"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Healthcare_Resource_Group</xref>
      </b>
  
    <b>4</b>
. Failure to correctly populate this data element is likely to result in an incorrect 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/healthcare_resource_group.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Healthcare_Resource_Group</xref>
, usually associated with lower levels of healthcare resource.  </p>
  <p>
For further information, please refer to the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nhs_digital">NHS Digital</xref>
 website at: 
    <xref href="https://digital.nhs.uk/services/secondary-uses-service-sus/payment-by-results-guidance"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Payment by Results Guidance</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <b>
         <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_organisation_code__code_of_provider_">ORGANISATION CODE (CODE OF PROVIDER)</xref>
 will be replaced with 
      <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_organisation_identifier__code_of_provider_">ORGANISATION IDENTIFIER (CODE OF PROVIDER)</xref>
, when it has been approved for use in national information standards.    </b>
  </p>


  </body>
